{
  "stem": "2522.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On September 1, 1939, I was in a Hashomer Hatzair camp in the Tatra Mountains, very close to the Polish border.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I think, since the age of seven, I used to go to a Hashomer Hatzairian camp every summer.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That took about four weeks and then the rest of the summer I spent with my family and visiting relatives, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, just that in the morning, when, when we raised the flag, the usual thing, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [NON-ENGLISH], who was the-- who was the [NON-ENGLISH] and the head of the camp, passed around that the war broke out and that we'll have to close down the camp.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And everybody go home because it was not clear what would happen.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was not clear whether the Germans would be entering Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So the camp got closed that day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Went home by train.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Nothing.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nothing, just my father's anxieties were up.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother was very much perturbed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It wasn't clear what would happen.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Starting in '39, it was quite clear that the Slovaks who were collaborating with the Germans wanted to, to make a separate deal with the Germans to create an independent Slovak state.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This was after Munich.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This is after the Germans already occupied the Sudetenland and-- where Hitler indicated that he would destroy Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But in the conversation, it became clear that perhaps Slovakia would be treated differently than, than Bohemia.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "After all, Slovak did not have the armaments industry.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So again, this was part of the rationalization.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Well, maybe things are going to be different here in Slovakia than elsewhere.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For a period of time, life continued.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] A number of Jews left, not too many.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
